fields.title: Though it Seems Quite Fine
fields.description: What is 'Autumn'? you may ask, though the answer will leave you in tatters. For autumn is nature's own call to prepare itself for death and burial. Deep stuff.

fields.title: The Soul Ages Relentlessly
fields.description: Sad as it seems, the autumn reminds us that we are aging, and treading the path that leads us to the ultimate nowhere. See how much emotional depth I have?

fields.title: All Paths Lead to Winter
fields.description: And each path, no matter where you begin...will end somewhere.  In nature, winter is always approaching.  Grim, deep, stuff.

fields.title: If a Tree Falls in the Forest
fields.description: We all know the ancient question...but the truth is still unknown.  Like most truths in our so-called lives.  Grim, weighty stuff.
